1
00:00:02,609 --> 00:00:10,115
Badminton, is a game played as singles (where one person plays against one person) or doubles (where two people play against two people).

2
00:00:10,115 --> 00:00:15,771
The object of the game is for you or your team to win 2 sets faster than your opponent.

3
00:00:15,771 --> 00:00:20,164
To win a set, you must score 21 points and be at least two points ahead.

4
00:00:20,164 --> 00:00:26,260
If the scores are 20-20 for example, the game carries on until one player or pair has a two point lead.

5
00:00:26,260 --> 00:00:28,804
Okay then, so how do you score these points?

6
00:00:28,804 --> 00:00:39,890
To score a point, you must aim to hit the shuttlecock, which is usually cork with feathers with your racket over the net and onto your opponent's floor without the opponent returning the favour.

7
00:00:39,890 --> 00:00:47,531
The court is 13.4m long and 6.1m wide, and the net is 1.55 m above the ground.

8
00:00:47,531 --> 00:00:52,159
Pay attention to these lines, as the boundaries are different for singles and doubles.

9
00:00:52,159 --> 00:00:56,652
To start the game, a player must serve the shuttlecock below the waist.

10
00:00:56,652 --> 00:01:02,027
The shuttlecock must travel over the net and land in the areas defined for a serve to be legal.

11
00:01:02,027 --> 00:01:06,019
If the shuttlecock is hit onto the lines - this also counts as a point.

12
00:01:06,019 --> 00:01:10,638
The opponent will then try and return the shuttlecock and make you miss returning it back.

13
00:01:10,638 --> 00:01:13,412
This can go back and forth and is known as a 'rally'.

14
00:01:13,412 --> 00:01:20,213
Remember, the aim of the game is to hit the shuttlecock onto your opponents floor, and these are the area's you're aiming for.

15
00:01:20,213 --> 00:01:23,561
There are several shots you can utilise to try and win points.

16
00:01:23,561 --> 00:01:32,537
These include: Forehand ,backhand, slice, touch and smash.

17
00:01:32,537 --> 00:01:40,915
Hitting the shuttlecock over a net onto the floor so that your opponent can't return it sounds simple enough, but in badminton - it's very easy to lose points.

18
00:01:40,915 --> 00:01:43,706
There's a lot of things you can't do in badminton.

19
00:01:43,706 --> 00:01:47,522
You cannot hit the shuttlecock outside the area of play.

20
00:01:47,522 --> 00:01:50,028
You cannot hit the shuttlecock twice in succession.

21
00:01:50,028 --> 00:01:52,332
You cannot touch the net.

22
00:01:52,332 --> 00:01:56,293
You cannot hit the shuttlecock into the net and it land on your side of the court.

23
00:01:56,293 --> 00:02:04,030
You cannot touch the shuttlecock with any part of your body except with the racket and as earlier mentioned; you must serve the shuttlecock legally.

24
00:02:04,030 --> 00:02:08,227
If you commit any of these errors, this results in your opponents being awarded a point.

25
00:02:08,227 --> 00:02:12,727
Once a player or pair has won a point, they are also awarded the next serve.

26
00:02:12,727 --> 00:02:17,692
Once a player or a pair has won 21 points and is at least 2 points ahead, they win a set.

27
00:02:17,692 --> 00:02:21,288
First pair to win 3 sets faster than their opponent … wins.

28
00:02:21,288 --> 00:02:27,563
Now that's basically badminton in a nutshell, but there's a few things you'll need to understand before playing or going to a game.

29
00:02:27,563 --> 00:02:30,876
For example … Fault.

30
00:02:30,876 --> 00:02:39,044
At any point, if the referee notices any of these infractions: Let.

31
00:02:39,044 --> 00:02:43,098
Unlike Tennis, if the shuttlecock hits the net, it counts!

32
00:02:43,098 --> 00:02:47,028
Lets are generally called when something unexpected has interrupted.

33
00:02:47,028 --> 00:02:49,792
Here's a list of common lets.

34
00:02:49,792 --> 00:02:53,504
In this case, the point must be replayed.

35
00:02:53,504 --> 00:03:03,514
30th Point If in the rare instance that a score reaches 29-29, the person who scores the 30th point wins the set without having to gain a two point lead.

36
00:03:03,514 --> 00:03:06,014
As you can tell, Badminton is an extremely fast sport and it looks difficult, but as you watch or play Badminton, the rules will become clear.

